definitions.definition: ( uncountable ) Enmity , ill feeling ; ( countable ) a feeling of animosity or a dispute .

( uncountable ) Irritation or resentment awakened by a social injury or slight ; offence , especially taken in an emotional sense with little consideration or thought ; ( countable ) especially in fit of pique : a transient feeling of wounded pride .
( countable , obsolete ) In pique of honour : a matter , a point .

main_definition: ( uncountable ) Enmity , ill feeling ; ( countable ) a feeling of animosity or a dispute .

definitions.definition: ( card games ) In piquet , the right of the elder hand to count thirty in hand, or to play before the adversary counts one .
